# 4. 特訓開始！

Airi: So, Haruka, Shizuku, I want you two to teach me how to dance.
Shizuku: You want me to teach you, Airi...?
Haruka: I understand your reasoning, but do you really think we'll be able to help?
Shizuku: Right... I've always thought that your dancing was more technically sound than mine, Airi.
Airi: Yeah, but to be fair, I've only been learning dance techniques that suit me until now.
Airi: For example, how to make myself visible to the audience despite not being all that tall.
Minori: Oh, you taught me how to do that before!
Minori: I feel like my dancing has improved a ton ever since!
Airi: Yeah, it has. I also believe it was worth teaching you that since it's so practical.
Airi: But... I can't be the idol I want to become if I keep focusing on those kinds of things.
Shizuku: The idol you want to become...?
Airi: I want to be an idol who can not only really spread my wings on variety shows...
Airi: But one that can also deliver hope by blowing the audience away with my performance.
Minori: ...!
Airi: Of course, I've been doing what I can until now, and I haven't been settling for second place.
Airi: But I know that I won't be able to become the idol that I want to be at this rate. ReLight's performance made that all too clear...
Airi: I realize now that I won't be able to blow people away with my performances the same way the idols I looked up to when I was little did if I don't change how I do things.
Airi: I need to start making a real effort to become the ideal version of myself.
Airi: Which is why I need you two to help me... You're the closest to achieving that goal and you both have something that I don't.
Shizuku: Airi...
Minori: S-Sorry to interrupt...! But I'd also like to make the same request!
Haruka: Minori...?
Minori: I know I'm just piggybacking on what Airi just said, but I'd also like for you two to teach me!
Minori: I feel like if I can master the things Airi has taught me along with what I can learn from you guys, then I'll grow even more as an idol...!
Haruka: We can't really say no after being told that, can we?
Shizuku: No, we can't. And I'd like to do what I can for you two!
Minori: *Gasp*
Airi: Thank you both so much!
Haruka: But don't expect us to go easy on you. From now on, we're going to refine your techniques every day, starting with the foundations.
Airi: Good! I wouldn't have it any other way!
Minori: M-Me neither!
Haruka: Your arms are still too stiff.
Haruka: To put it bluntly, the way you're holding them out makes it look robotic.
Haruka: Think of your arm as two separate parts. One above your elbow and one below. Try spreading your arms while paying attention to how that joint moves!
Airi: Got it...!
Airi: (This is hard... We're just raising our arms in the air, but this is a total workout...)
Airi: (Still, this does make us seem more graceful. I mean, this must be why Haruka and Shizuku are able to exude an aura of elegance...)
Airi: (Also...)
Airi: (These are movements where I can apply the techniques I've cultivated so far. I need to make the most of this chance to learn!)
Shizuku: It's wonderful how your poses feel fun and energetic, but try to use your whole body to exude a more elegant impression.
Shizuku: The position of your limbs is important, but so are their angles. This helps lead the viewer's eye to where you want them to look. Let's try it together.
Minori: Wow!
Airi: (One subtle motion and I'm looking right where she wants. That was so clean and precise.)
Airi: (Even if I copied her exactly, there's no way the current me would be able to achieve the same result...)
Airi: (But I will be able to as long as I don't give up. So, I've just gotta keep trying...)
Minori: Nooo! I'm losing balance!
Shizuku: A-Are you okay, Minori?! Did I push you too hard?
Minori: N-No, I'm okay! That was all my fault!
Minori: So, please! Could we try that again?
Haruka: Okay. Why don't we call things here for today?
Shizuku: We'll try to come up with different exercises for tomorrow. For now, nice work, you two.
Minori: Th-Thank you!!!
Airi: I didn't think there were this many muscles I never used before.
Minori: S-Same here... My body's gonna be aching all over tomorrow...
Haruka: You two are drenched in sweat. Why don't you go grab a couple of towels? I'll mix up some protein for you two in the meantime.
Minori: Wait, really?! You're even helping us with muscle building? Thank you so much, Haruka!
Airi: A recovery drink does sound nice. Alright, let's go grab those towels...
Shizuku: Hehe... Airi and Minori worked so hard today.
Haruka: Yeah, also...
Haruka: You seem really happy, Shizuku.
Shizuku: That's because I am! When Airi asked me to teach her how to dance, I honestly wasn't sure if I'd be able to help her...
Shizuku: But I feel really happy right now because my skills and experiences are benefitting her and Minori.
Haruka: Right... Teaching them has also been a nice learning experience, so I'm glad we decided to do this.
Haruka: (But that's not all...)
Airi: I realize now that I won't be able to blow people away with my performances the same way the idols I looked up to when I was little did if I don't change how I do things.
Airi: I need to start making a real effort to become the ideal version of myself.
Airi: Which is why I need you two to help me... You're the closest to achieving that goal and you both have something that I don't.
Haruka: (Airi was completely serious...)
Haruka: (ReLight's performance was also an eye-opener for me, but what compelled me to become a better idol was actually...)
Haruka: I need to learn from their example.
